        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria",
        "description": "The k-omega SST turbulence closure and the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model are identified as the primary model-form choices. Literature review documents that SST has been validated for rotodynamic blood-pump flows in at least 6 peer-reviewed studies. Sensitivity of RH to turbulence model selection (SST vs. RNG k-epsilon) is quantified and found to be <12% across all operating points. Achieved level 2 confirmed by model-form justification memo."
      },
      "rationale": "Model-form selections are justified by peer-reviewed literature and sensitivity analysis, meeting the MRL 2 requirement for documented model-form rationale with quantified sensitivity."
