  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-cpb-dr-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team-2024",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepts the CFD hemolysis model for the stated COU (identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at MRL 2) based on the following structured evidence: (1) All 11 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels, with three factors (Discretization Error) exceeding the required level, providing additional confidence in numerical accuracy. (2) Two factors (Numerical Solver Error, Use Error) are formally scoped out with documented rationale: solver correctness is subsumed by the SQA and Numerical Code Verification assessments, and use-error risk is mitigated by institutional governance controls (SGP-CFD-2023-04) and mandatory peer review. The scoping decisions are consistent with ASME V&V 40 guidance for MRL 2 Class II device assessments where model influence is MEDIUM. (3) Validation results demonstrate agreement between CFD predictions and experimental hemolysis measurements within the combined uncertainty band at all 5 operating points, with GCI < 5% confirming numerical accuracy. (4) The provenance chain is complete: model inputs are traceable to the FDA-published geometry and measured fluid properties; validation data are traceable to documented experimental test reports; and all simulation activities are recorded under the institutional simulation governance procedure. (5) No weakeners were identified in the structured review. The team concludes that the model is fit for the stated regulatory purpose and that the credibility evidence is sufficient to support the 510(k) submission claim that RH < 1 relative to the predicate device."
  },
